('e9bcdb14-182d-43a9-84b8-0f5a61d81bb5', '201971ce-3266-4b06-9973-3c753ec502b3', '558fd281-7d22-4b42-864c-9227ab45a2a6', 'Faced with this, the individual holds the line to their BATNA, trading patience for leverage and refusing to move first, and true to form remembers every surprise as something they saw coming all along.', 'Revisits the same decision from a new angle each time doubt resurfaces, even after nominally deciding. The counterparty is reading every hesitation as information.', 'Something closer to mild interest than alarm, resolving into performative calm — that never really rises to the level of a feeling at all.', 0.74, '4556417e-ac86-4549-833b-d3a75bd358ee'),
('213c216f-2d03-4b65-9adb-15b8f5ffd4bf', '8c297dc7-dc2c-42c5-ad03-cc218bdc029d', '2ad86ede-13d2-49b6-a383-57aac3d9a2c0', 'Faced with this, this person lets the numbers set the floor and refuses to negotiate against itself, and true to form discounts their own exposure to the risks they warn others about.', 'Treats the choice as a small research problem: gather the knowable facts first, model the downside, then commit only once the math stops moving. The relationship and the number are both on the table at once.', 'A flat, measured pulse with no real spike, resolving into euphoric overreach — that is essentially forgotten by the next decision.', 0.68, '4556417e-ac86-4549-833b-d3a75bd358ee')
